  "rationale": {
    "chat_summary": "UK 230V single-phase domestic dwelling, TN-C-S, Ze=0.35Ω, PSCC=6kA. 5 final circuits sized per BS 7671:2018+A2:2022 App 4 + App 12: 2× 2.5 mm² rings + 1.5 mm² upstairs lighting (vd_cumulative binding at 22m radial per App 12) + 6 mm² cooker + 2.5 mm² immersion. All copper PVC singles. CPC sized per Reg 543.1.3 + Table 54.7 — adiabatic passes. calc.cable_ampacity + calc.voltage_drop + calc.cpc_adiabatic deferred per WI3.",
    "sections": [
      {
        "title": "Project Supply + Jurisdiction",
        "summary": "GB jurisdiction → BS 7671:2018+A2:2022 governs. Single-phase 230V TN-C-S supply from DNO with declared Ze=0.35Ω and PSCC=6kA. Consumer unit CU-MAIN feeds 5 final circuits direct (no sub-feeders). Engineer accepts DNO declared values; runtime tool calls deferred per WI3."
      },
      {
        "title": "Cascade Tree + Topology",
        "summary": "Flat topology: CU-MAIN root with 5 final-circuit children (C01-C05). No feeders or sub-feeders — typical UK domestic 'flat-cascade' below the cut-out. Each node carries parent_node_ifault_ka=6.0 from the DNO PSCC declaration (engineer's worst-case proxy until calc.fault_level resolves)."
      },
      {
        "title": "Walk-the-Ladder Approach + Binding Constraints",
        "summary": "Four circuits (C01, C02, C04, C05) bind iz_vs_in: starting csa already large enough to satisfy Iz ≥ In (Reg 433.1) given OCPD rating. C03 (lighting radial, 22m, 6A MCB) binds vd_cumulative: 1.0 mm² rejected at 3.4% > 3% lighting limit; 1.5 mm² accepted at 2.2%. Trail shows one rejected + one accepted entry."
      },
      {
        "title": "Cumulative Voltage Drop",
        "summary": "App 12 §G: lighting circuits limited to 3% (≈6.9V at 230V); power/cooker/heating limited to 5% (≈11.5V). No upstream sub-feeders so vd_segment_pct = vd_cumulative_pct for every node. C03 the only constraint-binding circuit at 2.2%; remaining circuits comfortably below their 5% limits."
      },
      {
        "title": "CPC Adiabatic Sizing",
        "summary": "Reg 543.1.3 + Table 54.7: CPC selected to be capable of carrying the prospective earth-fault current for the OCPD operating time (0.4s ADS for final circuits in dwellings). Sizes per Table 54.7 (phase ≤16 mm² → CPC = phase): 2.5/1.5, 1.5/1.0, 6/2.5. All pass adiabatic check (tool_call_pending true)."
      },
      {
        "title": "Motor Starting + Parallel Cables + Harmonic Derating",
        "summary": "Not applicable. No motor loads (load_type=motor) — all circuits are general power / lighting / heating / cooker. parallel_count=1 throughout (domestic CSAs ≤6 mm²). No high-harmonic loads declared, so harmonic_ch_applied omitted. motor_starting_vd_pct and motor_starting_vd_pass null on every node."
      },
      {
        "title": "Compliance + Assumptions + Tool-Call Pending",
        "summary": "compliant=true. One info-severity flag on C03 documenting the vd_cumulative walk-up. Assumptions: Ze and PSCC verified at cut-out per DNO declaration. Three tool calls (calc.cable_ampacity / calc.voltage_drop / calc.cpc_adiabatic) deferred per WI3; engineer Iz_corrected and Vd values are placeholder estimates pending deterministic resolution."
      },
      {
        "title": "Cross-Skill Contract",
        "summary": "Emits cable-sizing intent with 5 circuit records carrying phase_csa, cpc_csa, material, insulation, cable_type, length_m, installation_method, r1_plus_r2 and reactance per metre at operating temperature. Future consumers: cable-schedule (tabulated), riser (parent-child render), cable-containment (tray/conduit fill), small-power v1.1 (Zs resolution)."
